{"questionId":"9908","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The number of brown squirrels, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> , in an area of woodland can be modelled by the following&nbsp;differential equation.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{d}}x}}{{{\\text{d}}t}} = \\frac{x}{{1000}}\\left( {2000 - x} \\right)\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1000</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2000</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>, where&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x > 0\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>One year conservationists notice that some black squirrels are moving into the woodland.&nbsp;The two species of squirrel are in competition for the same food supplies. Let <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span> be the&nbsp;number of black squirrels in the woodland.</p>\n<p>Conservationists wish to predict the likely future populations of the two species of squirrels.&nbsp;Research from other areas indicates that when the two populations come into contact the&nbsp;growth can be modelled by the following differential equations, in which <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span> is measured in&nbsp;tens of years.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{d}}x}}{{{\\text{d}}t}} = \\frac{x}{{1000}}\\left( {2000 - x - 2y} \\right)\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>x</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1000</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2000</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;≥ 0</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{d}}y}}{{{\\text{d}}t}} = \\frac{y}{{1000}}\\left( {3000 - 3x - y} \\right)\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>y</mi>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1000</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>3000</mn>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>3</mn>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;≥ 0</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">An equilibrium point for the populations occurs when both&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{d}}x}}{{{\\text{d}}t}} = 0\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{d}}y}}{{{\\text{d}}t}} = 0\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>When the two populations are small the model can be reduced to the linear system</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{d}}x}}{{{\\text{d}}t}} = 2x\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{d}}y}}{{{\\text{d}}t}} = 3y\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>t</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>For larger populations, the conservationists decide to use Euler’s method to find the long‑term&nbsp;outcomes for the populations. They will use Euler’s method with a step length of 2 years (<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t = 0.2\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.2</mn>\n</math></span>).</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Use further iterations of Euler’s method to find the long-term population for each&nbsp;species of squirrel from these initial values.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>number of brown squirrels go down to 0,&nbsp;<br>black squirrels to a population of 3000&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9908","referenceCode":"SPM.3.AHL.TZ0.2d.iii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Use further iterations of Euler’s method to find the long-term population for each species of squirrel from these initial values.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d.iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.16—Eulers method for 1st order DEs"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}